{"author":{"id":"11f56c2e7a2cb634892b4cf7e5d51bdc88cfe8b0eb217f0aae7f836b6d88fc66"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1561336768,"nonce":"AMw2hdUmdz+AcrMIBRvZgj2R8VY=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU0NTk2Mzc0NDQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2467","origin":"github"},"title":"deseq2 fails on pulsar runner.","message":"Hi all,\n\nIt seems as though the new version of deseq2 is incompatible with Pulsar.\n\nPulsar will transfer to the remote location all `*.R` files only if they are mentioned in the `deseq2.xml` file. As `get_deseq_dataset.R` is not, it doesn't get transferred by pulsar and so the job fails. \n\n`get_deseq_dataset.R` is referred to in `deseq2.R` but not in the `deseq2.xml` file.\n\nTo get around this on my server I have added a `touch '${__tool_directory__}/get_deseq_dataset.R' \u0026\u0026` line to the start of the command tag in the xml file. It forces pulsar to transfer over the file.. \n\nShould we make the change in deseq2?","files":null}]}